  "description": "Erhard Valentin Bergström was a Swedish editor and writer who was born on January 4, 1897, in Eskilstuna, Sweden. He was married for 25 years to Hilda Oljeqvist and had two children. Bergström was a well-traveled individual, having been to countries such as Italy, France, Iceland, Russia, and others. He worked with various newspapers, including Södermanlands-Posten, Katrineholms-Kuriren, Hudiksvalls Nyheter, and Hudiksvalls-Posten, where he served as an editor for over 15 years. Bergström was also a member of several organizations, including the North Hälsingland Animal Protection Society, the North Hälsingland Aviation Club, and the Society for Maintaining Lillfjärden's Bird Life. He wrote the book Birdlife in City Park Ponds and Watercourses in 1933 and received a gold medal from the Swedish Hunting Association and the 1st Hunting Trophy from the Gavle Hunting Society."
